Intro Definition: Mutual acknowledgement of certain multiple Gods (whatever the center) and intimate entanglement between their lores and cults defines a polycentric social field.
At a population level, that there is a &ldquo;multiplicity of positive existential commitments&rdquo; regarding the supreme deity is an empirical fact beyond dispute. Eg. Hinduism. Examples: Acknowledgement of multiple deities who can each be treated as the center is clear in the vedic lore. [MT]
